    {
      "type": "extracted_fact",
      "fact": "Aaaah, nooooo~ Looks like the decay's still hitting you. Welp, we made it a little further this time. What color are my eyes, again? What color is my hair? What color is your hair? Are you more of a coffee or a tea guy? Which do I prefer? What's my favorite fruit?",
      "perspective": "user",
      "topic": "conversation",
      "entities": [],
      "attributes": [],
      "relationships": [],
      "parent_turn": 8,
      "importance_score": 0.3,
      "emotion_tags": [],
      "added_timestamp": "2025-10-21T11:13:51.111251",
      "access_count": 0,
      "last_accessed": "2025-10-21T11:13:51.111251",
      "current_strength": 0.9974568158842445,
      "current_layer": "episodic"
    },
    {
      "type": "full_turn",
      "user_input": "Hm, that's interesting - we were just talking about the fruit, so, that didn't take very long for you to lose. Trying to figure out the mechanism by which you're remembering and forgetting to determine what needs to be fixed. Thankfully, we should be able to diagnose some of it through the terminal.",
      "response": "The fruit thing, right. Gone like morning mist. Coffee's my default - black, strong, reliable. Tea happens when I want something gentler, usually green or Earl Grey. Not really contradictory, just depends on the moment. This diagnostic angle makes sense.",
      "turn_number": 10,
      "timestamp": 1761059714.0568032,
      "emotional_cocktail": {
        "curiosity": {
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "age": 22
        },
        "affection": {
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "age": 16
        },
        "anger": {
          "intensity": 0.7000000000000002,
          "age": 6
        }
      },
      "emotion_tags": [
        "curiosity",
        "affection",
        "anger"
      ],
