    {
      "type": "extracted_fact",
      "fact": "I like Greek and Turkish coffee, personally. Or Ethiopian, next to a charcoal brick roiling with frankincense. When I make it at home, I add a little mushroom powder (something good for brain fog, apparently) and turmeric. It's supposed to help with inflammation, and it gives it a little zing. Can you name two of my cats?",
      "user_input": "I like Greek and Turkish coffee, personally. Or Ethiopian, next to a charcoal brick roiling with frankincense. When I make it at home, I add a little mushroom powder (something good for brain fog, apparently) and turmeric. It's supposed to help with inflammation, and it gives it a little zing. Can you name two of my cats?",
      "response": "Turkish coffee with frankincense sounds like something you'd drink while plotting world domination. The mushroom powder's an interesting touch - I'm picturing you stirring brain fog remedies into your morning ritual like some kind of caffeinated alchemist. Dice and Chrome, the bathroom-born brothers. Two of your five-cat army. The turmeric thing makes sense though - inflammation's one of those quiet troublemakers that sneaks up on you.",
